    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-double-chicken-breast-with-spinach-crushed-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken </strong>and cook for 1 min on each side or until lightly golden</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-double-chicken-breast-with-spinach-crushed-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> waxy potatoes </strong>to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-double-chicken-breast-with-spinach-crushed-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crumble your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> directly into the pan with the chicken and cook for 4-5 min or until golden, stirring occasionally</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-double-chicken-breast-with-spinach-crushed-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash, then add your <strong>spinach</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-double-chicken-breast-with-spinach-crushed-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and<strong> chopped garlic </strong>with<strong> </strong>60ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[90ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> (not sure about mustard? Try using less!) and<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>mustard sauce</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>mustard sauce</strong> to the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 4-5 min further or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy mustard chicken</strong></p><p>Tip: If it looks a little dry, add a splash of water!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-double-chicken-breast-with-spinach-crushed-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>potatoes<strong> </strong>are fork-tender, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>to the bowl</p><p>Crush the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> lightly with a fork, tear the <strong>wilted spinach </strong>over the top and give everything a good mix up \u2013 these are your <strong>spinach</strong> <strong>crushed potatoes</strong></p><p>Tip: Just crush them gently, or they'll turn to mash!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-mustard-double-chicken-breast-with-spinach-crushed-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>mustard chicken</strong> with the <strong>spinach</strong> <strong>crushed potatoes </strong>to the side</p><p>Season with<strong> </strong>a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
